<%#
# String Form Partial

This partial renders an input element for a string attribute.
By default, the input is a text field.

## Local variables:

- `f`:
  A Rails form generator, used to help create the appropriate input fields.
- `field`:
  An instance of [Administrate::Field::String][1].
  A wrapper around the String pulled from the database.

[1]: http://www.rubydoc.info/gems/administrate/Administrate/Field/String
%>
<%= f.label field.attribute, class: "block mb-2 text-sm font-medium text-gray-900" %>
<%= f.text_field field.attribute, class: "form-control block w-full px-3 py-1.5 text-base font-normal text-gray-700 bg-white bg-clip-padding border border-solid border-gray-300 rounded transition ease-in-out m-0 focus:text-gray-700 focus:bg-white focus:border-sky-600 focus:outline-none" %>
